00:13:08.390 --> 00:13:10.099
you were gonna let me
get this out to my fan.

252
00:13:10.100 --> 00:13:11.350
Of course not.

253
00:13:11.351 --> 00:13:12.853
"I've been where you've been.

254
00:13:12.978 --> 00:13:14.645
Talk to me. I'm here."

255
00:13:14.646 --> 00:13:17.941
You're beginning to sound like
your old self. Lee.

256
00:13:19.484 --> 00:13:21.902
That was the point. I want
to keep his attention on me

257
00:13:21.903 --> 00:13:23.572
because. as long
as he's focused on me.

258
00:13:23.697 --> 00:13:25.616
then he's too distracted
to kill anybody else.

259
00:13:25.741 --> 00:13:27.575
- I can stop him.
- Look.

260
00:13:27.576 --> 00:13:29.869
until we have the confidence

261
00:13:29.870 --> 00:13:31.454
that you're willing
to work with us.

262
00:13:31.455 --> 00:13:33.707
we have to limit your access
to the outside world.

263
00:13:33.832 --> 00:13:35.709
How much more limited
can my access possibly be?

264
00:13:35.834 --> 00:13:39.171
Your visitors are restricted
to the family members

265
00:13:39.296 --> 00:13:41.465
you've already agreed
to talk to. and that's it.

266
00:13:45.052 --> 00:13:46.344
Hey now.

267
00:13:46.345 --> 00:13:48.388
It's family therapy time.

268
00:14:02.402 --> 00:14:03.362
Mr. Voit.

269
00:14:04.780 --> 00:14:07.698
My name is Joshua Ryan.

270
00:14:07.699 --> 00:14:10.869
Deena Ryan was my cousin.

271
00:14:11.870 --> 00:14:13.413
Her mom was already here.

272
00:14:13.538 --> 00:14:15.374
Her parents are divorced.

273
00:14:15.499 --> 00:14:17.876
I-I'm here on behalf
of her father. Alex.

274
00:14:19.503 --> 00:14:21.587
To be honest.

275
00:14:21.588 --> 00:14:24.632
Alex doesn't think
he can trust himself around you.

276
00:14:24.633 --> 00:14:26.718
Well. if you loved
your cousin Deena so much.

277
00:14:26.843 --> 00:14:29.095
what makes you think that you
can trust yourself around me?

278
00:14:29.096 --> 00:14:32.015
Well. nothing can change
what you did.

279
00:14:33.642 --> 00:14:35.852
Nothing can bring Deena back.

280
00:14:35.977 --> 00:14:37.186
So. you want to punish yourself?

281
00:14:37.187 --> 00:14:39.313
Hear all
the excruciating details

282
00:14:39.314 --> 00:14:41.358
of how I made her suffer
before she died?

283
00:14:41.483 --> 00:14:44.403
I came here to understand you.

284
00:14:45.529 --> 00:14:48.198
This is gonna sound peculiar.
but as it so happens.

285
00:14:48.323 --> 00:14:50.492
after Deena disappeared.
back in 2006.

286
00:14:50.617 --> 00:14:53.494
I became totally engrossed

287
00:14:53.495 --> 00:14:56.998
in the details
of her police investigation.

288
00:14:57.124 --> 00:14:59.917
And when her case ran cold.
I turned

289
00:14:59.918 --> 00:15:02.295
my attention
to other unsolved crimes.

290
00:15:02.421 --> 00:15:04.380
Kind of. uh.
researching them. actually.

291
00:15:04.381 --> 00:15:07.926
Uh. from there. I decided
to enroll in night school.

292
00:15:08.051 --> 00:15:09.761
where I took classes
in criminal justice.

293
00:15:09.886 --> 00:15:11.011
forensics. sociology.

294
00:15:11.012 --> 00:15:13.139
All of which led me to earning

295
00:15:13.140 --> 00:15:17.018
my PhD in criminology.

296
00:15:17.936 --> 00:15:19.855
Congratulations. Doctor.

297
00:15:19.980 --> 00:15:23.066
The thing is.
my family doesn't want Deena

298
00:15:23.191 --> 00:15:24.401
to have died in vain.

299
00:15:24.526 --> 00:15:27.319
We feel if there's
something. anything

300
00:15:27.320 --> 00:15:28.362
the world can learn.

301
00:15:28.363 --> 00:15:29.740
if there's some way to ensure

302
00:15:29.865 --> 00:15:32.116
this never happens again.

303
00:15:32.117 --> 00:15:34.702
that's what we want.

304
00:15:34.703 --> 00:15:39.206
So are you gonna write a book?

305
00:15:39.207 --> 00:15:42.626
None of them tell the truth.

306
00:15:42.627 --> 00:15:45.172
The truth.

307
00:15:46.423 --> 00:15:48.300
It was quick and easy.

308
00:15:49.301 --> 00:15:51.136
Nothing to write a book about.

309
00:15:51.928 --> 00:15:54.388
I met her in a bar.
I took her to a motel.

310
00:15:54.389 --> 00:15:56.390
Strangled her. I wrapped her up.

311
00:15:56.391 --> 00:15:58.727
I stuffed her
in a shipping container.

312
00:15:59.561 --> 00:16:02.981
Mr. Voit. obviously.
you're under no obligation

313
00:16:03.106 --> 00:16:05.065
to share what you know with me.

314
00:16:05.066 --> 00:16:07.319
but as I said. my family...

315
00:16:08.320 --> 00:16:10.529
...at the very least.

316
00:16:10.530 --> 00:16:13.158
we deserve to hear the truth.

317
00:16:17.245 --> 00:16:19.289
Come back tomorrow.

318
00:16:19.414 --> 00:16:20.916
Why?

319
00:16:21.041 --> 00:16:23.001
Because I said so.

320
00:16:31.718 --> 00:16:34.471
<i>Joshua Ryan. You buy that?</i>

321
00:16:34.596 --> 00:16:37.097
Somebody had to vet him. right?

322
00:16:37.098 --> 00:16:38.809
Well. somebody
had to get Deena's dad

323
00:16:38.934 --> 00:16:42.186
to sign off on that guy
before he walked in here

324
00:16:42.187 --> 00:16:43.979
to represent.

325
00:16:43.980 --> 00:16:46.525
but I don't see you
yelling for the warden

326
00:16:46.650 --> 00:16:51.570
to let you call the BAU and
tell them you found your fan.

327
00:16:51.571 --> 00:16:53.739
So they can do what exactly?

328
00:16:53.740 --> 00:16:56.951
Oh. I don't know. arrest him?

329
00:16:56.952 --> 00:16:58.661
For what?

330
00:16:58.662 --> 00:17:01.038
Do you honestly think.
if they searched his home.

331
00:17:01.039 --> 00:17:02.457
his office. or you-name-it.

332
00:17:02.582 --> 00:17:04.209
they'd find a shred of evidence
tying him to murder?

333
00:17:04.334 --> 00:17:08.546
What about all those souvenirs
he's been collecting

334
00:17:08.547 --> 00:17:11.966
since even before
he stepped over the line?

335
00:17:11.967 --> 00:17:14.803
Just like the ones you took.

336
00:17:14.928 --> 00:17:19.057
He's not leaving that shit on a
shelf somewhere in plain sight.

337
00:17:19.182 --> 00:17:22.143
He has a special place
just for himself.

338
00:17:22.269 --> 00:17:25.730
where he can admire them
and relive the thrill.

339
00:17:28.483 --> 00:17:31.193
And if the BAU
could find that place?

340
00:17:31.194 --> 00:17:34.113
They'd have everything
they need to put him away.

341
00:17:34.114 --> 00:17:37.033
You think he'd tell you
where it is?

342
00:17:37.909 --> 00:17:39.494
If he trusts me.

343
00:17:40.996 --> 00:17:42.539
Why?

344
00:17:45.000 --> 00:17:47.377
Because he's like me.

345
00:17:47.502 --> 00:17:49.295
Deep down. he's lonely.

346
00:17:49.296 --> 00:17:52.048
and he wants to share.

347
00:18:04.769 --> 00:18:06.104
- Hey.
- Hey.

348
00:18:07.355 --> 00:18:08.939
Thanks.

349
00:18:08.940 --> 00:18:10.900
How's. uh. Deputy Duran doing?

350
00:18:10.901 --> 00:18:13.570
Feeling as if he woke up with
the worst hangover in his life.

351
00:18:13.695 --> 00:18:15.822
Was he able to tell you anything?

352
00:18:15.947 --> 00:18:19.783
All he remembers is the suspect
pulling over in this sedan.

353
00:18:19.784 --> 00:18:21.578
getting out.
raising their hands.

354
00:18:21.703 --> 00:18:24.205
and as he and Deputy Colwater
were about to slap on the cuffs.

355
00:18:24.331 --> 00:18:25.831
it was lights out.

356
00:18:25.832 --> 00:18:28.334
The tox panel confirms
the presence of etorphine.

357
00:18:28.335 --> 00:18:31.045
And the puncture wound
in his back suggests he was hit

358
00:18:31.046 --> 00:18:33.589
with a one-and-a-half-inch
tranquilizer dart.

359
00:18:33.590 --> 00:18:35.759
That would've had to been fired
with an air rifle.

360
00:18:35.884 --> 00:18:37.718
From a second unsub.

361
00:18:37.719 --> 00:18:39.386
An air rifle isn't really
the weapon of choice

362
00:18:39.387 --> 00:18:41.513
for the Lugo Cartel
targeting law enforcement.

363
00:18:41.514 --> 00:18:44.558
No. it isn't.
These unsubs aren't targeting

364
00:18:44.559 --> 00:18:46.226
any and every cop.

365
00:18:46.227 --> 00:18:49.147
They spared Duran and
targeted Colwater specifically.

366
00:18:49.272 --> 00:18:53.442
Which means... setting aside
all the victims were deputies...

367
00:18:53.443 --> 00:18:55.694
there's a connection in the
victimology that we're missing.

368
00:18:55.695 --> 00:18:57.197
Yeah. you're right.

369
00:18:57.322 --> 00:19:00.075
And considering the degree of
torture and the manner of death.

370
00:19:00.200 --> 00:19:03.244
I'd say that connection
is deeply personal.

371
00:19:08.583 --> 00:19:11.293
How's it going with
the missing dash cam footage?

372
00:19:11.294 --> 00:19:14.421
The ethereal wireless connection
to the cumulous cloud

373
00:19:14.422 --> 00:19:17.968
pregnant with precious data
has been impeded. remotely.

374
00:19:18.093 --> 00:19:19.678
So. my guess is the evil-doers

375
00:19:19.803 --> 00:19:23.055
made that happen
just after they figured out

376
00:19:23.056 --> 00:19:24.556
who the deputies' vehicles were.

377
00:19:24.557 --> 00:19:26.475
Even though that sounds
pretty sophisticated.

378
00:19:26.476 --> 00:19:28.978
like something
drug traffickers might do...

379
00:19:28.979 --> 00:19:30.646
Not to mention highly illegal.

380
00:19:30.647 --> 00:19:33.732
which also drug dealers
have a big affinity toward.

381
00:19:33.733 --> 00:19:35.151
and just the facts.

382
00:19:35.276 --> 00:19:37.696
signal jammers
are a terrifyingly common

383
00:19:37.821 --> 00:19:39.406
- e-commerce purchase.
- Yes.

384
00:19:39.531 --> 00:19:41.949
I thought so. I want you to come
with me and bring your laptop.

385
00:19:41.950 --> 00:19:44.660
Wait. aren't we supposed to look
at the dash cam?

386
00:19:44.661 --> 00:19:46.120
No. No. there's something else.

387
00:19:46.121 --> 00:19:48.748
Oh. Okay. Um...

388
00:19:48.873 --> 00:19:52.793
Hold on. Just getting my things.
So many things.

389
00:19:52.794 --> 00:19:55.505
So many things.
Here I come. Coming.

390
00:19:57.257 --> 00:20:00.135
Why are we being secret?

391
00:20:00.927 --> 00:20:02.553
Something about this case

392
00:20:02.554 --> 00:20:03.972
hasn't sat well with me
since we got here.

393
00:20:04.097 --> 00:20:06.640
- Sheriff Chambers?
- For a start.

394
00:20:06.641 --> 00:20:10.227
Can we all agree
this violence seems personal?

395
00:20:10.228 --> 00:20:12.062
As if motivated by retaliation.

396
00:20:12.063 --> 00:20:15.525
Or retribution.
Which is why. Penelope.

397
00:20:15.650 --> 00:20:18.485
I need you to start reviewing
all of the personnel records

398
00:20:18.486 --> 00:20:20.320
of the Lupold County
Sheriff's Department.

399
00:20:20.321 --> 00:20:21.698
starting with our three victims.

400
00:20:21.823 --> 00:20:23.616
Got it. What am I looking for?

401
00:20:23.742 --> 00:20:26.577
Try to identify
any unusual patterns

402
00:20:26.578 --> 00:20:28.246
in disciplinary actions

403
00:20:28.371 --> 00:20:30.456
or even arrest records.

404
00:20:30.457 --> 00:20:33.543
But I do not want you
sharing your findings

405
00:20:33.668 --> 00:20:35.211
with anyone but us.

406
00:20:37.505 --> 00:20:40.466
Oh. that's the secret part.
Not even Sheriff Chambers

407
00:20:40.467 --> 00:20:41.801
should know that
I'm peeking around?

408
00:20:41.926 --> 00:20:43.510
No. Only us.

409
00:20:43.511 --> 00:20:45.721
Right. but there's gonna be
alerts and notifications.

410
00:20:45.722 --> 00:20:47.307
I'm sure there will be.

411
00:20:47.432 --> 00:20:49.600
And you want me to disable them.

412
00:20:49.601 --> 00:20:50.934
I smell what
you're throwing down.

413
00:20:50.935 --> 00:20:53.772
Thank you. And I want you
to help her.

414
00:20:54.856 --> 00:20:57.484
- Uh. no. no. That's not necessary.
- It is.

415
00:20:57.609 --> 00:20:59.026
She doesn't need me.

416
00:20:59.027 --> 00:21:01.529
I need you to work with her.

417
00:21:02.614 --> 00:21:05.700
As far as we know.
Deputy Colwater is still alive.

418
00:21:05.825 --> 00:21:09.203
and we work better and faster
as a team. so...

419
00:21:09.204 --> 00:21:11.372
I will leave you both to it.

420
00:21:53.456 --> 00:21:55.750
Well. the deputies'
arrest records are gonna tell us

421
00:21:55.875 --> 00:21:57.751
more. I assume.

422
00:21:57.752 --> 00:21:59.336
Right off the bat.

423
00:21:59.337 --> 00:22:03.048
each of these deputies have had
at least one complaint

424
00:22:03.049 --> 00:22:04.759
for use of excessive force.

425
00:22:04.884 --> 00:22:07.845
- Join the club.
- What?

426
00:22:07.846 --> 00:22:09.138
What?

427
00:22:09.139 --> 00:22:13.058
Excessive force in any situation
is not okay.

428
00:22:13.059 --> 00:22:14.477
A lot of cops
get that complaint.

429
00:22:14.602 --> 00:22:17.313
We have to make sure that
these aren't frivolous.

430
00:22:18.398 --> 00:22:20.858
- I need to say one thing.
- We don't need to talk about it.

431
00:22:20.859 --> 00:22:22.443
- Yes. we do.
- Now. look.

432
00:22:22.569 --> 00:22:24.611
Donnie Mallick
reached for his gun.

433
00:22:24.612 --> 00:22:26.280
If I didn't shoot him.
I'd be dead.

434
00:22:26.281 --> 00:22:30.952
What I did and what you did
are categorically different.

435
00:22:34.706 --> 00:22:37.666
Donnie Mallick
killed those girls

436
00:22:37.667 --> 00:22:40.127
and killed Gideon.
you knew that.

437
00:22:40.128 --> 00:22:42.796
And in your mind.

438
00:22:42.797 --> 00:22:45.465
if he went to prison.
he would become a legend.

439
00:22:45.466 --> 00:22:47.551
- He would've.
- Right. so

440
00:22:47.552 --> 00:22:49.595
it's better dead
than incarcerated.

441
00:22:49.596 --> 00:22:51.013
It's not the same thing.

442
00:22:51.014 --> 00:22:52.390
Isn't it. though? Isn't it
our messy little fingers

443
00:22:52.515 --> 00:22:54.141
on the scales of justice?

444
00:22:54.142 --> 00:22:55.601
'Cause you said that

445
00:22:55.602 --> 00:22:58.061
my testimony prevented justice

446
00:22:58.062 --> 00:22:59.689
for the families
of Voit's victims.

447
00:22:59.814 --> 00:23:02.983
Well. uh. news. uh. Gideon
had a family. too. He had Jill.

448
00:23:02.984 --> 00:23:05.236
He had Stephen.
You knew what their values were.

449
00:23:05.361 --> 00:23:07.822
So doesn't their
sense of justice

450
00:23:07.947 --> 00:23:09.574
deserve to be served. too?

451
00:23:10.992 --> 00:23:11.992
You're right.

452
00:23:11.993 --> 00:23:14.078
- Yeah. I know I'm right.
- No.

453
00:23:15.246 --> 00:23:16.747
I mean. in the victimology.

454
00:23:16.748 --> 00:23:19.417
If we were looking
for suspicious behavior

455
00:23:19.542 --> 00:23:21.586
shared by the deputies

456
00:23:21.711 --> 00:23:24.254
who-who were on the job.
it would be buried

457
00:23:24.255 --> 00:23:27.383
in the arrest records
under something stupid like

458
00:23:27.508 --> 00:23:29.760
traffic stops.

459
00:23:29.761 --> 00:23:32.722
Filter under the phrase
"Reasonable Suspicion."

460
00:23:33.556 --> 00:23:35.265
Daniel Salazar.
it looks like he was

461
00:23:35.266 --> 00:23:37.143
pulled over a bunch of times
by all of our deputies.

462
00:23:37.268 --> 00:23:38.435
not a single citation.

463
00:23:38.436 --> 00:23:39.562
Where is he right now?

464
00:23:39.687 --> 00:23:40.896
Uh. Salazar owns

465
00:23:40.897 --> 00:23:42.982
the Seven Gems Gentlemen's Club.

466
00:23:43.107 --> 00:23:44.775
which I'm sure
is anything but gentle.

467
00:23:44.776 --> 00:23:46.777
We need to chat
with Mr. Salazar.

468
00:23:46.778 --> 00:23:48.571
Just sent you his info.

469
00:24:01.042 --> 00:24:02.501
I told you.

470
00:24:07.924 --> 00:24:09.841
Can I get you something?

471
00:24:09.842 --> 00:24:11.928
We are looking for the owner.

472
00:24:12.720 --> 00:24:14.097
That don't sound too good.

473
00:24:14.222 --> 00:24:16.516
Daniel Salazar?

474
00:24:16.641 --> 00:24:18.267
May I say who's asking?

475
00:24:18.268 --> 00:24:20.770
FBI. I'm S.S.A. Tara Lewis.

476
00:24:20.895 --> 00:24:22.187
S.A. Tyler Green.

477
00:24:22.188 --> 00:24:24.022
<i>Órale.</i> Should I call my lawyer?

478
00:24:24.023 --> 00:24:26.192
No. We just want to talk.

479
00:24:26.317 --> 00:24:28.193
Let's talk.

480
00:24:28.194 --> 00:24:30.655
You recognize these deputies?

481
00:24:31.739 --> 00:24:34.574
- It's a small town.
- I'll take that as a yes.

482
00:24:34.575 --> 00:24:36.535
Department records show
you were pulled over

483
00:24:36.536 --> 00:24:38.997
by each one of these officers
on separate occasions.

484
00:24:39.122 --> 00:24:40.873
and yet. you were never cited.

485
00:24:40.999 --> 00:24:44.294
Seriously? They actually logged
my traffic stops?

486
00:24:44.419 --> 00:24:46.253
Yes. they did.

487
00:24:46.254 --> 00:24:48.047
Those are some
dumb motherfuckers.

488
00:24:48.172 --> 00:24:51.008
Well. maybe that's why Deputies
Banks and Hernández are dead

489
00:24:51.009 --> 00:24:52.843
and Deputy Colwater
was abducted last night.

490
00:24:52.844 --> 00:24:55.012
What the fuck you talking about?

491
00:24:55.013 --> 00:24:58.516
Mr. Salazar. you know what I see
when I look around this place?

492
00:24:58.641 --> 00:25:02.269
A very turquoise laundromat.

493
00:25:02.270 --> 00:25:03.521
I mean. I'd say you were

494
00:25:03.646 --> 00:25:05.188
making a killing
laundering money in here.

495
00:25:05.189 --> 00:25:07.816
but if I had to guess.
I would say that

496
00:25:07.817 --> 00:25:09.401
plus a little sex trafficking.

497
00:25:09.402 --> 00:25:11.903
- Oh. should we throw in drug trafficking?
- Mm.

498
00:25:11.904 --> 00:25:14.573
All on behalf
of the Lugo Cartel.

499
00:25:14.574 --> 00:25:16.200
And see.
someone wants us to think

500
00:25:16.326 --> 00:25:19.328
that it's the Lugo Cartel
that killed two deputies

501
00:25:19.329 --> 00:25:21.455
- and abducted a third.
- Not me.

502
00:25:21.456 --> 00:25:23.541
I got no beef with these dudes.

503
00:25:23.666 --> 00:25:25.459
But you do know what
all of these traffic stops

504
00:25:25.460 --> 00:25:26.418
look like. don't you?

